C:\Data\Nucleus_Dev\Vostok_ACU_A\source\XCategory\Application\all\API013RemoteFunction\API013RemoteFunction.c
      1          /**
      2           * @file
      3           * @brief       Communications to control application-layer remote functions.
      4           *
      5           * @details     The same API013RemoteFunction module is used on the client and the server.
      6           *                  Client Declarations:
      7           *                      API013_CLIENT_FEATURE should be ENABLED
      8           *                      API013_SERVER_FEATURE should be DISABLED
      9           *                  Server Declarations:
     10           *                      API013_CLIENT_FEATURE should be DISABLED
     11           *                      API013_SERVER_FEATURE should be ENABLED
     12           *              Using the same module on the client and server helps ensure that the client and
     13           *              server are using the same type and version of the API.
     14           *
     15           *              API013RemoteFunction allows each client to control one or more remote function
     16           *              servers that each controls one or more remote functions. For each of the remote
     17           *              functions, the API manages three types of data:
     18           *                  - Controls
     19           *                  - Background Function
     20           *                  - Status (that can be handled as events)
     21           *                  - Data Acquisition
     22           *
     23           *              Control (Required by each Remote Function):
     24           *              Each remote function must support the following standard controls:
     25           *                  - Control Command 0 = Disable the remote function
     26           *                  - Control Command 1 = Enable the remote function
     27           *              The remote functions can have additional application-specific control commands
     28           *              with command-specific parameters.
     29           *
     30           *              Background Function (Optional for each Remote Function):
     31           *              Each remote function may provide a background function that will only be called
     32           *              while the remote function is enabled.
     33           *
     34           *              Status / Events (Optional for each Remote Function):
     35           *              Each remote function may implement a status message. If implemented, the first
     36           *              status byte must indicate whether the remote function is enabled (1) or disabled
     37           *              (0). The remote function may have additional application-specific status
     38           *              information.
     39           *              A remote function can generate an event by publishing a status message that was
     40           *              not requested by the client.
     41           *
     42           *              Data Acquisition (Optional for each Remote Function):
     43           *              A client may setup periodic publication of server data. A server will publish all
     44           *              available data channels from all enabled servers at each publication.
     45           *
     46           * @copyright   Copyright 2016-2017 Whirlpool Corporation.  All rights reserved - CONFIDENTIAL.
     47           */
     48          
